branch_name: Banque Populaire - JXQP+5V8, Marrakesh
review:
Opinion on my recent experience at the Ibn Tofa√Øl agency

A loyal customer for many years, I went to your agency yesterday to make a simple cash withdrawal. My experience was unfortunately frustrating for several reasons:

Lack of clear signage at the counters:
Three counters were open, but no sign or indication specified the services offered at each. I chose an ATM at random and, after a few minutes of waiting, the teller informed me that it was not the right place for withdrawals. With profits of 3.5 billion DHR in 2023, is it not possible to invest in simple signs to guide customers?

Unreasonable waiting time:
After reaching the right counter, I waited more than 20 minutes even though there were only two customers in front of me. The slowness of the service was mainly due to the unavailability of a manager, essential to validate an operation. This absence paralyzed the process.

Incomprehensible administrative requirements:
Finally arriving at the counter to make my withdrawal, providing my account number and my national card, I was asked... for the passport used when opening the account. This appears to be a ‚Äúregulatory‚Äù requirement. However, this passport has obviously expired (every passport in the world expires after a certain time) for years and is therefore no longer in my possession. Such a request is both illogical and a source of frustration, especially since the ID presented proves my identity indisputably.
Following my objection, the manager told me that my current passport could be suitable. So there‚Äôs the pompom! They quote me the regulations (passport used when opening the account) and then, we take the liberty of not respecting them, we accept another passport, but not a national card!!!

These various points reflect a total lack of consideration for customers and a lack of organization. A visit to an agency should be simple, quick and efficient, especially for routine operations such as withdrawals.

A soon to be ex-client of the Banque Populaire

branch_name: Bmci - 67 Av. Mohammed V, Ouarzazate
review:
On July 31, around 2:20 p.m., I went to the BMCI branch to carry out a currency exchange. I had left my wife and daughter in the car, and I was in a hurry because of the intense heat outside. In addition, I had to fill up with diesel and therefore had to pay the gas station in euros, as I was unable to change my currency.

At the BMCI branch, an employee informed me that she was eating and that it would take 30 minutes to serve me. The way he responded was unprofessional, which left a very negative impression on me.

Later, I took my currency exchange to the Banque Populaire branch in Agdz, where I was served like a king. I strongly advise Moroccans and foreigners to avoid this BMCI agency, because the customer service leaves something to be desired, especially in emergency situations or in high heat.

review: I recently had the distinct privilege of dealing with Mr. Soufiane Bouhadi  at Bank Assafa in Agadir, and his service was nothing short of exemplary. His exceptional professionalism, meticulous attention to detail, and unwavering commitment to excellence were evident throughout our interactions. Mr. Soufiane meticulously addressed every facet of my banking needs, ensuring a seamless and highly satisfactory experience. His expertise and dedication set a new benchmark in client service. I wholeheartedly recommend Mr. Soufiane for anyone seeking unparalleled service and a consummate professional.

review:
Assalam alaykom,

On August 13, 2024, I opened a bank account in their office. I can honestly say that the office is clean, organized and quiet. The bank employees are polite and the services are fast and convenient. There are no long waiting times. The bank manager Si Soufyan in particular was very attentive and helpful. He personally explained to me what Sharia finances are and personally opened my new account. If I could give more than 5 stars I would. This was one of my best banking experience in Morocco ever. Keep up the good work! Wassalam. N. El Otmani.

Its director, Mr Bouhadi Soufiane, stands out for his human approach and attentive listening. He always took the time to answer my questions and advise me with expertise. Thanks to its leadership, the agency offers exceptional, warm and personalized service.
I highly recommend this agency to anyone looking for quality banking support! Thank you to the whole team for your excellent work!

review:
Well disappointment and frustration this time with the lack of response and assistance I have received from your customer service department or let‚Äôs say my ¬´¬†advisor¬†¬ª Karim serghouchni (CIH bank med 5) . Despite numerous attempts to contact your bank through phone calls and emails, I have not received any form of acknowledgment or resolution regarding my concerns.

I have been a loyal customer of CIH Bank for more than 8 years , and I have always appreciated the quality of service provided. However, the recent lack of communication has left me feeling neglected and unsupported. As a customer, I believe it is my right to receive timely and satisfactory assistance when I encounter issues or have inquiries, especially having given the assigned advisor who never responded on working hours and when he does he responded on non working hours and then he complained that he supposed not answer since he‚Äôs out of duty, but when he‚Äôs on duty he never answer which is confusing.

I have diligently followed the recommended channels to seek help, but my efforts have been met with silence. This experience has caused me significant inconvenience and has left me uncertain about the status of my requests. I trust that this is not the level of service CIH bank  intends to provide to its valued customers.

I kindly request that you investigate the matter promptly and provide me with a comprehensive explanation for the lack of response. Additionally, I seek assurance that necessary steps will be taken to rectify this situation and improve the bank's customer service performance moving forward. Specifically I m speaking about my advisor Karim serghouchni who is working in CIH agadir med 5. He literally lacks the communication skills as he just responded to me in WhatsApp audio saying (ngolik a shrif ) which is not close to be a professional way of speaking to costumers, this pushed me to request to change my branch city.

I would appreciate your prompt attention to this matter. I believe in the importance of open communication and trust that you will take the necessary actions to address my concerns. I hope to receive a satisfactory resolution to restore my confidence in CIH bank  commitment to customer satisfaction.

20.06.2023

The bank indicated on its website that it is ‚Äúa comprehensive bank that keeps pace with its clients, whether they are individuals, professionals or companies.‚Äù
In Morocco, Islamic banks are called participatory banks, as they are not described, either in laws or in advertising campaigns, as Islamic banks.
The new bank said that it provides "a rich package of daily banking products and services, as well as financing, investment, employment, and savings products."

branch_name: Cr√©dit Du - Av. Fal Ould Oumeir, Rabat
review:
So clearly we can't just give 0.
Customer since 2008 in this bank with current account, currency, savings I can give you an idea of ‚Äã‚Äãthe circus that you will encounter there.

Positive point: Some nice agents by their nature and not the agency, unfortunately they end up leaving.

Dark spots:
-Reception, customer relations. Poorly trained agents, borderline unpleasant and condescending, completely unreachable remotely (telephone, whatsapp, text messages, emails... Telepathy!).
Unless you are retired and want to travel every day for any need, avoid this bank, and above all this agency would be a good thing for your mental health. Hanout atmosphere.
-Poorly adapted system: requesting an amortization table took 2 months, because the agency has to send a request to Casablanca and bla bla they go around in circles, so imagine having to respond elsewhere within a certain time frame.
-Bank customer since 2008, I have never received a promised call to respond to a need expressed to the agency, and the agent each time asks for my number which has never changed for 20 years which is on its screen
-No hierarchy: no way to escalate anything to anyone, the online site and the application are useless for reporting a problem because there is no monitoring, you can write as much as you want.... nada .
-No operation will take you less than 20 minutes, so be sure you won't have to do anything afterwards.
-The bank changes its clauses discreetly and illegally: I learn that I cannot take out a loan for no reason (probably because I am black). I contacted the business center then the management who ended up telling me yes you will have it but I asked again I was told "the final agreement is still not out" hhh clowns. Imagine if I had no other alternatives.

Brief
Soon I will close all accounts.

Update: there remains a current account, soon to be closed to put this mishap far behind.
dominant_topic: Op√©rations bancaires et acc√®s aux services

branch_name: Cr√©dit Du - Av. Fal Ould Oumeir, Rabat
review:
Bj,
Big disagreements with the agency head at C du M today.
Impossible to request euros if convertible account?
I didn't have this information. They explained that the rules had been changed.
Customer for 25, the staff leaves you unable to exchange Dhs for euros.
Instead of simply saying that the operation would be possible via a currency exchange office.
On the other hand, I just learned today that my convertible DHS account has been in debt since 2021... So I have a debt to Morocco's credit. The agios plus bank charges each period.
Uninformed, I am told that I will have to pay the various costs.
No information given to the customer.
And after a misunderstanding on my part regarding the fees for 2023 and 2024 we tell you: the account is frozen.
So if I don't pay for 10 years, the M' credit will offer me the account keeping fees and the agios.
Nice, but I don't think it's normal to look for the new banking rules as a customer.
We tell you that all this is written in the bank bulletin.
Dsl but I did not choose to be a bank employee and therefore impossible to have this information.
In another scenario Please, I asked several months ago why I had to pay several monthly payments in the same month on a loan.
A letter from the bank was indeed sent but no follow-up to the file.
In short, I was used to more generous services.
This is my dissatisfaction......especially since the address changes have been made.
In this bank it would be necessary to review the customer management policy regarding the new regulations and anticipate the difficulties in which customers might encounter.
Kind regards

Dsl
Difficulties a client might encounter.

branch_name: Umnia Bank - Av. Mohamed VI, El Jadida
review:
I am extremely disappointed with my experience with Umnia Bank. Here are the major problems I encountered:

Account opening: Opening my account at the El Jadida agency was slow and poorly managed. Despite a long wait with few customers in front of me, the process took a long time. Additionally, obtaining a copy of the contract proved complicated and unpleasant.

Inactive ecard: My ecard has remained inactive for more than two months despite my four visits to the agency. Repeated excuses such as system issues or staff absences never resolved this issue.

Difficulties with the Uconnect app: I had problems changing my password through the Uconnect app. Having forgotten the answer to the secret question, I contacted the agency to reset my password, but after two days of waiting, I still have no solution.

Due to these numerous malfunctions and the poor quality of service, I decided to close my account with Umnia Bank as quickly as possible. I do not recommend this bank due to its lack of organization and ineffective customer service.

If it had less than one star I would have rated it.
The worst agency in the history of banks. My father, a customer with them for over 20 years, they made him leave and come back every two days (for lack of CIN, data adjustment).
Also, they decided to block and reduce all bank card limits to zero even though I needed them at the supermarket.

A real disaster unworthy of being called a bank

branch_name: Bmci - Angle rue 9 et Av. Mohamed V, K√©nitra
location: Angle rue 9 et Av. Mohamed V, K√©nitra
review:
I would like to share a particularly disappointing experience that I had on Tuesday October 9, 2024, at 3:43 p.m., at the BMCI agency located at the corner of Avenue Mohamed V and Avenue Hassan II.
I went there to make a check withdrawal, even though I am not a customer of this particular agency. According to the schedules displayed on the BMCI website, the agency closes at 4 p.m., and I was therefore confident of arriving on time.
Unfortunately, the welcome I received from the cashier was unacceptable.
Her attitude was rude, and she communicated with a blatant lack of respect.
I had the impression of being a nuisance and being treated as an intruder, which is unbecoming of a bank with the reputation of BMCI.
This is not the first time that I have noticed a lack of professionalism in this agency, but this time pushed me to leave this review.
I am really disappointed with this type of service, and I think it can seriously damage the image of BMCI.
I sincerely hope that measures will be taken to improve the quality of welcome and service in this agency.

branch_name: Bmci - Angle rue 9 et Av. Mohamed V, K√©nitra

review: I was very disappointed with the service. Staff incompetent and unwilling to help, which caused significant delays in processing my requests. I hope the bank will take steps to improve the quality of their customer service, as this is key to retaining customers. New customers flee...

review:
The worst of all agencies! lousy service!!!. Most of the agents, including the agency manager, are absent and their service is poor! They can never be reached by telephone. Without going into too much detail about the mediocrity of their service and a scam of which I was the victim concerning a property insurance which was imposed on me after having completed a loan, in short I DO NOT recommend it to you AT ALL!!
If there was the possibility of not putting stars in the reviews I would not have hesitated to do so.

branch_name: Attijariwafa Bank - 36, avenue Tadla (aviation), Quartier. Mabella, El Youssoufia
location: 36, avenue Tadla (aviation), Quartier. Mabella, El Youssoufia
review:
Hello, I wanted to share with you my bad experience with this agency.
So I just created an lbankalik account made up of the SMART offer which is 100% "Free" and without account maintenance fees, but when I went to the agency to collect my bank card, the advisor told me added "Avenir Plus" life insurance for which a monthly contribution of 150 dhs is included as well as Epargne d'Or insurance with a monthly contribution of 300 dhs without any authorization, even though I only requested the pack of the offer SMART.
Fortunately I checked my account via the application, and paid attention to this error and the direct debit under the title "Avenir plus direct debit" applied to my account.
Today, when I requested a cancellation of these which are normally the fault of the agency advisor, as well as the reimbursement of the direct debit applied since it was in no way my fault, he refused to select the reimbursement, even he insisted that I continue to benefit from these insurances.
Ultimately, he canceled the insurances, but no refunds were applied.
First of all, with so many errors and problems, it gives a very bad impression towards the Attijari Wafabank Group and its credibility!

review:
I am extremely disappointed with the service offered by this agency. To certify a check, I followed their instructions and submitted an application as requested. However, they required that this request be written on letterhead, which seems unnecessary and unjustified to me in this specific case.

I had to wait a very long time for a service that was nevertheless simple. The staff was unwelcoming and unprofessional. My problem was only taken seriously after the intervention of an influential lady in the field, which is unfortunate for an ordinary customer.

As a customer, I expected more serious, rapid and respectful treatment.
This experience left me with a very negative impression, and I am now considering other banking options if improvements are not made.

I hope that the bank will take concrete measures to strengthen the quality of its services and better meet the expectations of its customers in the future.

branch_name: Cr√©dit Du - Av. Fal Ould Oumeir, Rabat
review:
So clearly we can't just give 0.
Customer since 2008 in this bank with current account, currency, savings I can give you an idea of ‚Äã‚Äãthe circus that you will encounter there.

Positive point: Some nice agents by their nature and not the agency, unfortunately they end up leaving.

Dark spots:
-Reception, customer relations. Poorly trained agents, borderline unpleasant and condescending, completely unreachable remotely (telephone, whatsapp, text messages, emails... Telepathy!).
Unless you are retired and want to travel every day for any need, avoid this bank, and above all this agency would be a good thing for your mental health. Hanout atmosphere.
-Poorly adapted system: requesting an amortization table took 2 months, because the agency has to send a request to Casablanca and bla bla they go around in circles, so imagine having to respond elsewhere within a certain time frame.
-Bank customer since 2008, I have never received a promised call to respond to a need expressed to the agency, and the agent each time asks for my number which has never changed for 20 years which is on its screen
-No hierarchy: no way to escalate anything to anyone, the online site and the application are useless for reporting a problem because there is no monitoring, you can write as much as you want.... nada .
-No operation will take you less than 20 minutes, so be sure you won't have to do anything afterwards.
-The bank changes its clauses discreetly and illegally: I learn that I cannot take out a loan for no reason (probably because I am black). I contacted the business center then the management who ended up telling me yes you will have it but I asked again I was told "the final agreement is still not out" hhh clowns. Imagine if I had no other alternatives.

Brief
Soon I will close all accounts.

branch_name: Cr√©dit Du - Av. Fal Ould Oumeir, Rabat
review:
Bj,
Big disagreements with the agency head at C du M today.
Impossible to request euros if convertible account?
I didn't have this information. They explained that the rules had been changed.
Customer for 25, the staff leaves you unable to exchange Dhs for euros.
Instead of simply saying that the operation would be possible via a currency exchange office.
On the other hand, I just learned today that my convertible DHS account has been in debt since 2021... So I have a debt to Morocco's credit. The agios plus bank charges each period.
Uninformed, I am told that I will have to pay the various costs.
No information given to the customer.
And after a misunderstanding on my part regarding the fees for 2023 and 2024 we tell you: the account is frozen.
So if I don't pay for 10 years, the M' credit will offer me the account keeping fees and the agios.
Nice, but I don't think it's normal to look for the new banking rules as a customer.
We tell you that all this is written in the bank bulletin.
Dsl but I did not choose to be a bank employee and therefore impossible to have this information.
In another scenario Please, I asked several months ago why I had to pay several monthly payments in the same month on a loan.
A letter from the bank was indeed sent but no follow-up to the file.
In short, I was used to more generous services.
This is my dissatisfaction......especially since the address changes have been made.
In this bank it would be necessary to review the customer management policy regarding the new regulations and anticipate the difficulties in which customers might encounter.
Kind regards

Dsl
Difficulties a client might encounter.

branch_name: Soci√©t√© G√©n√©rale, - Angle Bd Hassan II et Route Echouhada, Settat
location: Angle Bd Hassan II et Route Echouhada, Settat
review:
The following behavior is in no way representative of the Societe Generale des Banques Marocaines, but rather an individual case that is expressly attributable to the branch and the responsible person - branch manager!

The extent of impudence, there is no more degrading way to "greet" a customer.

At 9:23 the entrance door was still only half open because the cleaning lady was still cleaning at the entrance.

Out of politeness, I stopped and asked the cashier if it was open yet, to which she replied in the affirmative.

So I was just about to enter when the "security guard" appeared out of nowhere and stood in my way.

He didn't respond to my greeting, which in itself is extremely cheeky, but that's not how we're used to "security" in this country, and he boldly asked what I wanted. "I want to go into the bank." Apparently that wasn't enough for him, because the question was now asked the other way around: "What exactly do you want here...?".

Since banking matters are generally no one's business, especially not some third-class security guard who thinks he's Dirty Harry, I answer again: "I want to go to the bank." Discreet, normal tone. This leaves him unconcerned and he boldly asks for the third time. As a cultured person you give in at some point, and I then told him that I would like to transfer my account from Casablanca here.

That worked, and then got me a seat at the desk of the branch manager of this miserable branch.

As soon as I sat down I was left alone. When the lady came back, I asked her who this person - security guard - was and why I was treated so condescendingly even though there were already people inside. Then the cool comment: "That can't be right, you can't say anything against the good man."

This sat with me!! I stood up and simply said that I had no business here and that I would be better off changing banks.

As already mentioned - it's getting boring - you don't ask for much, but there should be a minimum of respect.

The reincarnation of indignity. Thank you Societe¬†General Settat Vol. Hassan II.

PS: I then went about 500m further to the Agence Societe Generale Lalla Aicha, and I can only be amazed at the difference. Polite, courteous, professional... Just the way it should be!

branch_name: Attijariwafa Bank - M443+74F, Oujda
review:
I would like to express my great disappointment with the customer service of the Banque du Maroc.
Having tried to change my phone number via the mobile application, my request was refused, forcing me to physically go to an agency. Living abroad, this involves taking a plane ticket, which is totally unacceptable for such a simple procedure.

Additionally, when I asked to speak to a manager to understand the situation, I was hung up on several times, and my attempts to call back went unanswered. This lack of consideration and efficiency is inexcusable and does not reflect the service that a customer has the right to expect.

I strongly advise against this bank, whose staff would rather hang up than resolve a problem. Although the application fee is always collected without fail, it is impossible to get help when you need it. This lack of professionalism is unacceptable.

I am requesting urgent customer service improvement and remote inquiry support for customers residing abroad.

branch_name: Banque Populaire - M3HG+654, Oujda
review:
I am a customer over 50 years old of the Banque Populaire d‚ÄôOujda. In December 2020 I went to Istanbul for medical treatment, the cash I took to cover medical expenses, I wanted to use my bank card with a tourist amount, all the ATMs refused the transaction.
By calling the head of the Al Wilaya d'Oujda agency (out of more than 40 calls) I was answered twice without any solution...
I sent a complaint to the CEO of the Banque Populaire d'Oujda on 01/06/2021, after 40 days of waiting, I was called to see the director (Ms. Belahcen) at 3:30 p.m. she left me waiting until 4:15 p.m. when I left. I call that negligence towards customers. This kind of behavior neither works in the interests of the bank nor the trust of its customers..
Leaving a customer hanging around in a foreign country with his money who cannot use it puts us in total distrust of this bank..

branch_name: Banque Populaire - 7C68+P2V, Av. Al Istiqlal, K√©nitra
review:
Last August, my mother, an elderly and respectful woman, went to this agency to withdraw the sum of 800,000 DHS, necessary to purchase an apartment. To our surprise, not only was she refused this operation without offering a solution, but she was also treated with a profound lack of respect. The employees had unpleasant words towards him, which is unacceptable.

The following month, she tried to make a transfer for the notary. Once again, she was met with a categorical refusal, without them bothering to listen or verify her request. He was abruptly asked to go to his original agency, located in Khenifra, a 5-hour drive from Kenitra. Worse still, a young employee spoke to her badly, making her even more stressed.

My mother, who suffers from high blood pressure, had to go to another agency located just 100 meters from this one. There, she was greeted with professionalism and was able to make her transfer without any difficulty.

I sincerely wonder: what is the point of opening an agency in the city center, near the notaries, if it is to refuse to help your clients and treat them with such contempt?

This experience was deeply shocking and disappointing for our family. I strongly recommend this agency to anyone who wants to be treated with respect and consideration.

branch_name: Wafa Bank - 7 Bd Hassan II, Tiznit
review:
Something is wrong, not just the ATM!

When I entered the bank to report that the ATM had debited my account in the amount of 3,000 Moroccan Dirhams, I was instructed to notify my branch in Mirleft. I insisted that the problem took place at their branch in Tiznit and that they should look into this matter. There were two Moroccan women who had had the same problem. Because they were direct clients of this branch, they received customer service. The initial lack of professional attention from the security guard and the staff members on the ground floor impelled me to report the incident to the local police.

Upon returning to the branch accompanied by two police officers, the treatment I received changed dramatically. I was escorted to see the director of the branch upstairs who then lavished me with utmost professional attention. He contacted my branch in Mirleft to alert them of the incident.

My branch has filed a complaint which will take some twenty days to resolve this matter‚Äînot three days as they had stated in Tiznit.

Let‚Äôs hope the money finds its way back into my account!

They LIED and STOLE $220 from me.

That of BD Abdelmoumen is particularly disappointing: lunch breaks which last for hours in a continuous schedule, departures on leave which block the smooth running of the agency (the other employees are obviously not trained enough to provide the entire service), no one ever picks up the phone when you call, lack of professionalism and listening in the relationship with the client, the agency employees communicate with each other from one office to another, shouting to be heard, without talk about the waiting time which can last several long minutes.
My advice, if you have the choice, it is better to opt for another agency, that of rue d'Agadir is an example to follow.

branch_name: Cr√©dit Du - Place des Taxis -Imm. Bakrim -Q.I., Agadir
review:
I would like to address this complaint to you concerning an unfortunate incident that occurred during my visit to the Agency.

In fact, I traveled to your agency to make a payment during my lunch break. However, when my turn arrived, the cashier suddenly closed her session and left the agency without informing me of the situation. I learned from a colleague that it was on lunch break, although the opening hours mentioned on Google indicate that you remain open permanently until 4 p.m.

I left the other side of town, specifically to go to this agency based on the information available online. This situation was not only a waste of time (1 hour waiting on site), but also a total lack of respect towards me.

I expressed my dissatisfaction on site and asked to make a complaint, but I was advised to wait for the manager.

I am disappointed to see such a lack of quality of service. I hope that you will take the necessary measures to avoid the recurrence of such incidents in the future (provide 2 cashiers for example or indicate that you are closed)

review:
The staff operating at this agency have always served me well, especially the director who is extremely kind, but today the young, arrogant and irresponsible cashier showed me a lack of respect, even daring to refuse to serve me under the pretext that he will close to have lunch even though I was the only customer in the bank.
Faced with this feeling of contempt and humiliation because of the behavior of the cashier, I expressed my anger in my own way. It was then that the director of the agency intervened to force the cashier to make my transfer immediately and despite the latter continuing to provoke me in front of all the staff.
This kind of cashier is unworthy of working in such a well-reputed bank that respects its customers.

branch_name: Banque Populaire - 9CRP+FGW, Agadir
review:
Disappointing customer experience in this Elwifaq agency in Agadir.
- The waiting list system does not work, which leads to frustration and long waits.

- The file that I had prepared and sent online for the creation of my account never arrived at the agency, thus causing an unnecessary delay and a waste of time for everyone.

- The agency appeared to be facing major IT problems. The printer was not working, preventing necessary documents from being printed, and the remittance system was out of service, making any financial transaction impossible. These technical malfunctions not only prolonged the process but also created an atmosphere of chaos and incompetence.

- Another point to note: the lack of chairs, not only did I have to stand while creating my account, but this was also the case for a large part of the customers present. This made the wait even more painful.

However, I would like to point out that Mrs Bizgarn, the advisor, was really helpful and attentive despite these difficult conditions. She did her best to help.

I hope that this feedback will be taken into account to improve the waiting conditions and services of this agency.

branch_name: Umnia Bank - El Khattabi et, Angle Bd Abdelkrim, Bd Moulay Rachid, Marrakech
location: El Khattabi et, Angle Bd Abdelkrim, Bd Moulay Rachid, Marrakech
review:
Good morning,

Here is some feedback which I hope will help many people avoid disappointment.

If I could give 0 stars I would of course do so!

Context :

As part of the acquisition of real estate, I wanted to go through an "Islamic" bank for my credit application

Result :

When creating my account everything went pretty well, I explained the context well, namely that I don't have much time and that I wanted to apply for credit with Umnia

I am given the documents to bring back, everything is fine, my file is done, so I take it back to the customer service representative who tells me a deadline of 3 weeks

3 weeks later, I come back to ask if the answer has arrived
Advisor's response: no, the analyst hasn't looked at it yet, I still had to come so that the advisor could look in her space to see the progress of the file

But at that moment, I tell myself that a little delay is not serious

So I come back a week later, we take the same ones and we start knowing again I'll come back because otherwise I could die to get an answer
The advisor waits for me to come to look in her space, I tell her however that it would not be bad to restart and that basically I was told 3 weeks and that I had made it clear that I had a time constraint

I'll pass you the round trips with the same result that I no longer count

After a while, I start to lose my patience and I point out that it is not serious to wait for me to come to restart
To wait for me to come and not pick up your phone to keep me informed
And clearly not respecting the deadline initially given
And finally that with other banks it is max 10 days

Response from the advisor:

The deadline is for information purposes only.
It's not me, it's the analyst, I can't do anything except restart
If you are not happy go see the agency director
Well go to the other bank

So, I go see the agency director who is there for 10 minutes during the day at the office and I explain the situation to him.

Director's response:

Okay, I'm going to restart on my own and I'll call you back tomorrow

The next day of course no response

in the end, hang on, tell me, see the advisor who was not at all aware that the file had been given back to her and who did not want to take it back

In short, seeing the seriousness of the director we understand the behavior of the advisors

Summary of the operation:

I got my file back
I wasted 2 months of my time
I lost money in taxis
I lost 8,500 dhs of tax exemption because of the time it took Umnia

review:
I went there to exchange USD. The service was very slow to begin with. However, I need my money exchanged so I waited.
I handed over my USD and she did the math in the computer and did not give me a receipt but rather counted my money and handed over to me. The money seemed less than the exchange rate posted so I asked for my receipt. She gave me my receipt after a dirty look plus another 200 dirham. I looked up my total on the receipt and counted my money again and I was still short 80 dirham. I asked her again and this time she got all pissed off. Took the money from me and finally gave me the correct amount. This is my 14th day in morroco and so far this was the only time I was about to get scammed and that with a famous bank.

Avoid if possible please.
